    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <head>211. Telegram 752 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d211fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–2155. Official Use
                        Only; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-21"
                            >September 21, 1955, 10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d211-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d211-1"/>
                <p>752. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Deptel 757.</p>
                <p>Name second Chinese listed apparently incomplete as received. Confirm whether it
                    Lee Cheng-Wu (repeat Lee Cheng-Wu).</p>
                <p>Total number Chinese who departed US (repeat US) on Cleveland September 17 would
                    be useful to me for next meeting if available.</p>
                <p>Helpful for me receive figures (not names) Chinese departing US (repeat US) as
                    promptly after their leaving as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Shillock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
